Subject: [PATCH 1/9] bridge: port capacity_wake + 7 leaf modules toward TS
 parity
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First pass at porting the typescript/src/bridge/ folder to Python.
Phase 0 + the trivial-leaf subset of Phase 1 of the per-folder parity
plan: ports modules with zero cross-folder dependencies plus the
asyncio cancellation-pattern de-risking spike.

New modules:
- capacity_wake.py — asyncio.Event substitute for TS AbortSignal
  merge-and-wake pattern (port of bridge/capacityWake.ts)
- types.py — consolidated Protocols, dataclasses, and constants
  for BridgeConfig, SessionHandle, SessionSpawner, BridgeLogger,
  ReplBridgeHandle, WorkResponse, etc.
- session_id_compat.py — cse_/session_ tag translation with shim gate
- debug_utils.py — secret redaction, error formatters, log_bridge_skip
- bridge_enabled.py — entitlement gates (stubbed to defaults; no
  GrowthBook in the Python build)
- bridge_permission_callbacks.py — wire-format BridgePermissionResponse
  TypedDict + type guard + Protocol
- inbound_messages.py — user-message extraction + image-block mediaType
  normalization with inlined magic-byte format sniffer
- poll_config_defaults.py — PollIntervalConfig dataclass + defaults

Extensions:
- exceptions.py — adds BridgeFatalError(status, error_type) for the
  Phase 3 bridgeApi.ts port
- __init__.py — re-exports 32 Phase 1 symbols while preserving the
  legacy archive-metadata re-exports for test_porting_workspace.py

99 new tests, all passing. 270/270 bridge tests pass overall.
Legacy test_porting_workspace.py (23 tests) still passes.

The orchestrators (replBridge, remoteBridgeCore, bridgeMain) and the
HTTP client (bridgeApi) remain unported; planning docs live in
my-docs/get-parity-by-folder/ (local-only, gitignored).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
